quran[70]{c,v,t}:
  26,111,"They said: should we believe in you while the meanest (and the worst) follow you"
  26,112,"He said: I have no knowledge of what they used to do"
  26,113,"Their account is only upon my Master, if you realize"
  26,114,And I do not drive away the believers
  26,115,I am only a clear warner
  26,116,"They said: Noah, if you do not stop, you shall become among the stoned ones"
  26,117,"He said: my Master, indeed my people denied me"
  26,118,"so judge decisively (or open an opening) between me and them, and save me and anyone who is with me of the believers"
  26,119,So We saved him and anyone with him in the loaded Ark
  26,120,Then afterward We drowned the rest
  26,121,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,122,And your Master is certainly powerful and merciful
  26,123,(People of) Aad denied the messengers
  26,124,"when their brother Hud said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,125,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,126,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,127,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,128,Do you build a sign on every high place to fool around
  26,129,And you take up castles that you may live forever
  26,130,"And when you attack, you attack as tyrants"
  26,131,So be cautious of God and obey me
  26,132,And be cautious of the One who helped you with what you know
  26,133,He helped you with livestock and children
  26,134,and gardens and springs
  26,135,Indeed I am afraid of the punishment of a great day upon you
  26,136,"They said: it is the same to us whether you advise or are not of the advisors"
  26,137,this is only character of the earlier ones
  26,138,and we will not be punished
  26,139,"So they denied him, then We destroyed them. Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,140,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,141,(People of) Thamud denied the messengers
  26,142,"when their brother Salih said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,143,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,144,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,145,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,146,Would you be left safe (and secure) in what is here
  26,147,In gardens and springs
  26,148,and plantations and a palm tree with its ripe (and delicious) fruit cluster
  26,149,and houses you skillfully carve out of the mountains
  26,150,So be cautious of God and obey me
  26,151,and do not obey order of the excessive ones
  26,152,those who commit corruption on the earth and do not reform
  26,153,"They said: you are only of the bewitched ones"
  26,154,"you are only a human being like us, so bring a miracle if you are of the truthful ones"
  26,155,"He said: this is a (female) camel, she has (a portion of) drink and you have your (portion of) drink, on a known day"
  26,156,And do not touch her with harm otherwise the punishment of a great day takes you
  26,157,"So they killed her, then they became regretful"
  26,158,"Then the punishment took them. Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,159,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,160,People of Lot denied the messengers
  26,161,"when their brother Lot said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,162,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,163,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,164,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,165,Do you approach the males among humankind
  26,166,"And you leave what your Master created for you as your wives? No, but you are people who exceed the limits"
  26,167,"They said: Lot, if you do not stop, you shall be of those driven out"
  26,168,"He said: indeed I am of those who despise your action"
  26,169,"My Master, save me and my family from what they do"
  26,170,So We saved him and his family altogether
  26,171,except an old woman (his wife who was) among those staying behind
  26,172,Then We destroyed the others
  26,173,"And We poured down a rain on them, and it was an awful rain on those who were warned"
  26,174,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,175,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,176,The inhabitants of the woods (people of Midian) denied the messengers
  26,177,"when Shu'aib said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,178,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,179,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,180,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"